Character sheet for 2D cut-out animation, featuring "Bêli", an adorable baby lamb mascot. Children's book illustration style. The sheet must be on a clean, flat, white background to isolate the character elements.

//--- PRIMARY STYLE ---// Soft digital watercolor style with a gentle paper texture. The outlines are NOT black; they are soft, thin colored pencil lines in a warm grayish-beige color. The entire mood is serene, innocent, and heartwarming. Pastel color palette.

//--- CHARACTER DESIGN: "Bêli" ---// An incredibly round and fluffy spherical body, like a single ball of cream-colored cotton. Short, simple legs. Large, soulful, dark expressive eyes with a single white dot for light reflection. No mouth, or a tiny, simple curved line for a smile. The fur is a warm, creamy off-white. Soft pink inner ears and occasionally, subtle pink blush on the cheeks.

//--- REQUIRED VIEWS AND POSES (all on the same image) ---// 1. Full body "T-Pose": The character facing forward, with arms (front legs) extended to the sides. This is essential for animation rigging. 2. Side View: The character standing, seen from the side. 3. Back View: The character seen from behind. 4. Action Pose - Joyful Leap: The character mid-jump, with a happy expression. 5. Action Pose - Sleeping: The character curled up in a tight, peaceful ball.

//--- REQUIRED EXPRESSION HEADSHOTS (separate heads on the same sheet) ---// A lineup of 4 separate headshots showing different expressions: 1. Curious: Head tilted to the side. 2. Sad: A single, large, stylized teardrop falling from one eye. 3. Amazed: Eyes wide, looking upwards in wonder. 4. Peaceful: Eyes closed with a gentle smile.

//--- FINAL INSTRUCTIONS ---// Emphasis on clear separation between each element on the sheet. High resolution. Clean design. Perfect for separating parts for digital puppetry.

